# Write A Letter To Dixon — mission context

## What this is

A playful **official diplomatic transmission** from the **Arcturian High Council** to **DJ Dixon**, formally requesting **backstage VIP access** at **DC10 Circoloco Opening Weekend, Ibiza**. The hook: *“We came 36.666666 light-years—we bought a website and everything.”*

**Live site:** [writealettertodixon.com](https://writealettertodixon.com)

## Tone and UX

- **Voice:** Diplomatic / classified briefing meets sci-fi camp—sincere fun, not corporate or generic “blog” tone.
- **Visual identity:** Classified document, paper, stamps, mono labels—keep new UI consistent with existing patterns in `app/src` (see `App.css`, document components).
- **Navigation labels:** **Official Letter** (the transmission), **Mission Updates** (relay notices / field reports; route `/mission-updates`), **Dossier** (about/meta). Legacy `/signals` redirects to `/mission-updates`.

## Where content lives

- **Mission update entries:** `app/src/content/missionUpdates.js` — add new items at the **top** of the array (newest first); support `body` as a string or array of paragraphs.
- **Main letter copy:** letter-related components under `app/src/components/` (e.g. `LetterBody.jsx`).

## Stack (for changes)

- **React 19** + **Vite 6**, workspace root builds `app/` via `amplify.yml` → **AWS Amplify**. Prefer small, focused changes; do not add unsolicited docs or refactors outside the task.

## When editing copy

- Prefer in-universe language (transmission, relay, field report, clearance, stardate-style dates where it fits).
- Avoid breaking accessibility: sufficient contrast on the dark page shell; use `aria-label` on links only when visible text is not enough.
